== bench stops on a non-zero exit code:
shit: 1:16: error: Builtin 'bench': the command `false` exited with status 1.
shit: note: Pass `--ignore-exit-code` to benchmark it regardless.
== the failure sets the exit status:
rc=1
== --ignore-exit-code keeps sampling a failing command:
Benchmark: false (3 runs)
== --no-shell --show-output forks the command directly:
direct
direct
direct
